<h1>The Walk</h1>

<p>The cleanest current-convention instance of the practice: <strong>sharibako</strong>, a
real project, its whole chain and hos rendered as the documents they are—frontmatter
visible, styled as the typed metadata it is, not hidden as if it were plumbing. Every
document here is <a class="chain-link" href="https://github.com/sageframe-no-kaji/sharibako">verifiable
in the public repo</a>.</p>

<h2>The arc, as state</h2>
<p>Unlike the canonical chain, an arc renders <em>state</em>. A closed ho promotes to gold
と the first time you witness its closure (the news rule, §9); a superseded ho renders
pre-flipped at gold@0.40 and never fires—recession, not promotion. Here is sharibako's
ho-04 arc:</p>

<div class="arc">
  {%- for node in corpus.arc %}
  <div class="arc-node">
    <a href="{{ node.url }}">
    {%- if node.state == "superseded" -%}
      <span title="superseded: recession, not promotion">{% koma 28, {"mode":"keyline","face":"promoted","tint":"#d2c5a0"} %}</span>
    {%- else -%}
      <span class="state-mark" data-record="{{ node.id }}" data-state="{{ node.state }}">
        <span class="flip">
          <span class="face face-front">{% koma 28, {"mode":"keyline","face":"front"} %}</span>
          <span class="face face-promoted">{% koma 28, {"mode":"keyline","face":"promoted"} %}</span>
        </span>
      </span>
    {%- endif -%}
    <span class="arc-label cjk">{{ node.label }} · {{ node.title }}</span>
    </a>
  </div>
  {%- endfor %}
</div>

<h2>The visible architecture change</h2>
<p>The most persuasive single thing the practice can show is a plan meeting reality on the
record. <a class="chain-link" href="{{ corpus.showcase }}">ho-04.6—plain-prompt init</a>
supersedes ho-04.4's dashboard surface. Open its <code>supersedes</code> marker to see what
fell beside what replaced it, side by side. Nothing is erased; the record moves forward only.</p>

<h2>The Kamae chain</h2>
<ul class="doc-list">
  {%- for d in corpus.walkKamae %}
  <li><a href="{{ d.url }}">{{ d.title }}</a> <span class="meta">{{ d.frontmatter.type or "kamae" }}</span></li>
  {%- endfor %}
</ul>

<h2>The hos</h2>
<ul class="doc-list">
  {%- for d in corpus.walkHos %}
  <li><a href="{{ d.url }}">{{ d.title }}</a> <span class="meta">{% if d.frontmatter.shape %}{{ d.frontmatter.shape }} · {% endif %}{{ d.frontmatter.status or "" }}</span></li>
  {%- endfor %}
</ul>
